        <para>By clicking on the <guibutton>Create</guibutton> button, you access the editor in the Basic Input Forms on the first tab, "Publication."</para>
        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/editor_top_basic.png" align="center" valign="middle" width="1000px"/>
        </para>
        <para>Clicking on the large <guibutton>Tamboti</guibutton> logo returns you to the search interface. Note that all input you have made is discarded.</para>
        <para>To see the Cluster web page, click the <guibutton>Cluster</guibutton> logo <!--For logos I used the format of buttons-->to the right.</para>
        <para>Clicking on <guibutton>Help</guibutton> opens the present search interface in another window or tab (depending on your browser settings), allowing you to work with your
            input and refer to the explanations at the same time.</para>
        <para>To the right, there is a status message: "Editing record of type Book, with the title Story of My Life, on the Publication tab, to be saved
            in/db/resources/users/editor," detailing which type of record you are inputting ("Book"), what its title is, on which tab you are
            editing it, and where it will be saved. 
            The title serves to remind you of what you are working with, even when you are not on the form
            where the title information is input.</para>
